MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: TEXT/PLAIN; charset=US-ASCII

The function find_initial_marking will introduce deadlock or safety
violations in examples with merge place on conflicting branches if all
incomming branches of the merge place are not marked in the initial
marking.  See the example: atacs/examples/er/marking_test.er.  The example
currently has a SAFETY VIOLATION on the rule (x1f-/1->ack2+/1) that is
introduced by the function find_initial_marking.  If the rule is initially
marked, then the example works correctly.  Thus, find_initial_marking
should not strip tokens in examples with correct markings.

egm

